The Chairman Committee on prevention and control of COVID-19 Yobe State who is also the state Deputy Governor Hon. Idi Barde Gubana (Wazirin Fune) has charged people to remain calm as the suspected case in Potiskum has been confirmed negative. Gubana while briefing the Journalists in Damaturu said after following all standard guidelines and protocols, the persons samples collected and sent to laboratory in Abuja has turned to be negative. The Deputy Gov. said, “I am happy to announce that the result of the test came out negative, as such the person does not have corona virus disease. He is currently doing much better and will soon be discharged.  “While we thank Allah (SWA) for the negative result, I wish to stress to the general public to ensure continues and frequent personal and environmental hygiene, especially frequent hand washing with soap under running water.” Gubana added.  Earlier on Friday, the vice chairman of the committee and commissioner for health Dr Mohammed Lawan Gana had earlier briefed journalists that a 30 year old truck driver, who came from Lagos to Potiskum on 2- April -2020 with symptoms of cough, fever and difficulty in breathing of six days duration has been isolated in the general hospital Potiskum. Dr Gana said following a quick response by the committee, the specimen of the suspected person was taken and sent to Nigeria center for disease control (NCDC) and World Health Organization (WHO) accredited laboratory Abuja and the result is expected in the next two days. The vice chairman allayed fear that such suspects could infiltrate into the society adding that contact tracing sub-committee is monitoring trending in case of an event assuring that the state standing committee is on top of the situation in Yobe.  